.TH "do_sigtimedwait" 9 "do_sigtimedwait" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
do_sigtimedwait \- wait for queued signals specified in @which
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" do_sigtimedwait
.BI "(const sigset_t *which "  ","
.BI "kernel_siginfo_t *info "  ","
.BI "const struct timespec64 *ts "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "which" 12
queued signals to wait for
.IP "info" 12
if non-null, the signal's siginfo is returned here
.IP "ts" 12
upper bound on process time suspension
